<item>
            <title>[LU-11355] Add Lustre trim support</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11355</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Similar idea of fstrim, use SSD as backend of Lustre filesystem might have performances&lt;br/&gt;
drop with gc running in the background.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We have mount option &apos;-o discard&apos;(etc) for ldiskfs to trigger discard automatically&lt;br/&gt;
whenever filesystem free some space, but as our benchmarking this could&lt;br/&gt;
introduce latency too, and also this is somehow out of control.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So it is desirable for administrators to do trim manually, for example&lt;br/&gt;
doing trim if system are idle.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
